Package eu.profinit.manta.connector.powerdesigner.model

Interface Entity<E extends Entity<E,S>,S extends SimpleModelObject>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CompositeModelObject<S>, Mappable, NamedObject, eu.profinit.manta.dataflow.generator.modeling.common.nodes.NodeMetadata
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConceptualEntity, LogicalEntity
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEntity, ConceptualEntityImpl, LogicalEntityImpl
    public interface Entity<E extends Entity<E,S>,S extends SimpleModelObject>
extends CompositeModelObject<S>
    An entity represents an object about which you want to store information. For example, in a model of a major corporation, the entities created may include Employee and Division. When you generate a PDM from a CDM or LDM, entities are generated as tables. It is an EER data model entity, that can be inherited from another corresponding entity.

    ddrobny
